definition: cat/CL:隻|只[zhi1]/(dialect) to hide oneself/(coll.) modem

sentences.english: Who’s the cutest kitty in the world?
sentences.chinese: 誰是這個世界上最可愛的貓咪呀？

sentences.english: Figg made him look at photographs of all the cats she'd ever owned.
sentences.chinese: 費格太太還非要他看她過去養過的幾隻貓咪的照片。

sentences.english: A cat has a round face.
Buy a cat a present and it will play with the wrapper for 10 minutes.
sentences.chinese: 給貓咪買個禮物，它也就玩10分鐘的包裝紙。
於是穆那查到了貓咪那裏。

sentences.english: When the cat saw me, she started mewing.
sentences.chinese: 貓咪看到我，就開始喵喵的叫。

sentences.english: Little kitty, I just got home.
The cat nuzzled up to my leg.
sentences.chinese: 貓咪在我的腿邊蹭來蹭去。

sentences.english: That little desert fox is cuter than all internet kittens &puppies rolled up together.
sentences.chinese: 那隻小沙漠狐比網上那些滾來滾去的小貓咪萌多了。

sentences.english: They almost die of laughing when old Mrs. Tomkins sits down upon the cat.
sentences.chinese: 當老湯姆金斯夫人坐到貓咪身上時，她們幾乎要笑死。

sentences.english: Cat's back humped when she saw a dog.
sentences.chinese: 貓咪見到狗後弓起了背。

sentences.english: Yoshida said she wants customers to enter the cats’ “space” in order to achieve relaxation.
sentences.chinese: 吉田說，她希望顧客走進貓咪的“天地”來放鬆自己。

sentences.english: The frail cat was taken to the vet for treatment.
sentences.chinese: 這隻虛弱的貓咪被帶到獸醫處進行治療。

sentences.english: As internet mimes go this one is definitely the cat's whiskers.
sentences.chinese: 要說最新的網絡模仿熱潮，絕對非貓咪鬍鬚照莫屬。

sentences.english: A 24-hour photo shoot was held to photograph and film the kittens for use on these plates.
sentences.chinese: 劇組光拍攝這些用在盤子上的貓咪就花了24個小時。
